<br>
SUVs are the most arrogant statement. The rest of the world pays much more than we do for gasoline, thanks to big money politics. Why do you think we have our fingers in every pie in the middle east? Why do you think we give a shit about Afganistan? Kuwatii? It's all about the oil folks. <br>
<br>
And it's why the Arab world doesn't like us.<br>
<br>
So explain to me how Joe American needs a 10 ton beast of steel that sucks up gas like there is no tomorrow (and who knows - with that attitude, maybe there won't be). I'm not saying that there are not farmers, or other people who need larger vehicles for work, for life, but when I drive around and see more than half the cars on the road are SUVs of some sort and know that most of these people are urban and you cannot tell me that their lifestyle demands this sort of transportation. What, they cannot get out of the fucking driveway without 4 wheel drive? <br>
<br>
